<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1186,1474]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Discussion and diagnosis. this species known only from males was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dominguez" box="[1179,1406,1261,1287]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34" refString="Dominguez, E. (1987) Dos nuevas combinaciones de Polymitarcyidae (Ephemeroptera), descriptas por L. Navas. Physis, B 45, 9 - 12." type="journal article" year="1987">
Domínguez (
<number box="[1333,1397,1261,1287]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. It constitutes the most Southern record of the genus. Illustrations of furcasternal protuberances (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1376,1298,1324]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="14.[151,270,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox="[243,1335,197,1049]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[232,1355,179,1069]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Tortopus zottai, male paratype. 24, genitalia, v. v. (f 1 and f 2 = forceps segment 1 and 2, k = knob, mf = median furrow, pe = penes, sIX = ninth abdominal sternum); 25, mesofurcasternal plates (fsi = furcasternal impression, fsp = furcasternal plates); 26 – 27, details of apex of penes; 28, detail of pedestal and base of forceps, v. v.; 29, pedestal; 30, pedestal and forceps (pd = pedestal, ps = parastilus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195436/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[1345,1376,1298,1324]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) and genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[268,453,1336,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="14.[151,270,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox="[243,1335,197,1049]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[232,1355,179,1069]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Tortopus zottai, male paratype. 24, genitalia, v. v. (f 1 and f 2 = forceps segment 1 and 2, k = knob, mf = median furrow, pe = penes, sIX = ninth abdominal sternum); 25, mesofurcasternal plates (fsi = furcasternal impression, fsp = furcasternal plates); 26 – 27, details of apex of penes; 28, detail of pedestal and base of forceps, v. v.; 29, pedestal; 30, pedestal and forceps (pd = pedestal, ps = parastilus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195436/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figs. 24, 26– 
<number box="[424,453,1336,1362]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
) are given. Male imagos can be separated from all other species of the genus by: 
<number box="[1411,1424,1336,1362]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
) fore wing length 12.0– 
<quantity box="[427,536,1373,1399]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="12.5">12.5 mm</quantity>
; 
<number box="[549,565,1373,1399]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
) parastyli at least 
<number box="[787,824,1373,1399]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times length of its base, slightly becoming thinner towards the apex (
<figureCitation box="[383,538,1410,1436]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="14.[151,270,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox="[243,1335,197,1049]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[232,1355,179,1069]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Tortopus zottai, male paratype. 24, genitalia, v. v. (f 1 and f 2 = forceps segment 1 and 2, k = knob, mf = median furrow, pe = penes, sIX = ninth abdominal sternum); 25, mesofurcasternal plates (fsi = furcasternal impression, fsp = furcasternal plates); 26 – 27, details of apex of penes; 28, detail of pedestal and base of forceps, v. v.; 29, pedestal; 30, pedestal and forceps (pd = pedestal, ps = parastilus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195436/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figs. 
<number box="[455,538,1410,1436]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="29.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="28.0">28–30</number>
</figureCitation>
); and 
<number box="[615,631,1410,1436]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="3.0">3</number>
) fused basal portion of penes relatively thin, distal portions not expanded (
<figureCitation box="[279,367,1448,1474]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="14.[151,270,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox="[243,1335,197,1049]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[232,1355,179,1069]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Tortopus zottai, male paratype. 24, genitalia, v. v. (f 1 and f 2 = forceps segment 1 and 2, k = knob, mf = median furrow, pe = penes, sIX = ninth abdominal sternum); 25, mesofurcasternal plates (fsi = furcasternal impression, fsp = furcasternal plates); 26 – 27, details of apex of penes; 28, detail of pedestal and base of forceps, v. v.; 29, pedestal; 30, pedestal and forceps (pd = pedestal, ps = parastilus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195436/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number box="[334,367,1448,1474]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
), becoming thinner toward apex (
<figureCitation box="[760,905,1448,1474]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="14.[151,270,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox="[243,1335,197,1049]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[232,1355,179,1069]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Tortopus zottai, male paratype. 24, genitalia, v. v. (f 1 and f 2 = forceps segment 1 and 2, k = knob, mf = median furrow, pe = penes, sIX = ninth abdominal sternum); 25, mesofurcasternal plates (fsi = furcasternal impression, fsp = furcasternal plates); 26 – 27, details of apex of penes; 28, detail of pedestal and base of forceps, v. v.; 29, pedestal; 30, pedestal and forceps (pd = pedestal, ps = parastilus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195436/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figs. 
<number box="[827,905,1448,1474]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="26.5" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="26.0">26–27</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
